step: nmea_field
    belongs to: nmea
    expects: fields, idx
    returns: value

    note: Safely extract a field by index from a split NMEA sentence.
    note: Returns "" if index is out of range.
    note: Also strips any trailing checksum (*XX) from the field.

    do:
        if idx is less than 0 or idx is greater than or equal to length of fields
            return ""

        set value to fields[idx]

        note: Strip trailing checksum if present
        set star_pos to -1
        call index_of with value, "*" storing result in star_pos
        if star_pos is greater than or equal to 0
            call slice with value, 0, star_pos storing result in value

        call trim with value storing result in value
        return value
